name: Bao Express
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'If you looking for the correct style of food. Sorry, it is not. Fancy enough but nothing related to the food.

Their service was super quick, my dishes were delivered within 5 minutes after my order. All the food were cold when they arrivd my table.

Not tasty enough. The bun meat was dry and small portion, which a qualified meat bun shoul be meaty with juice. This style Chinese food should serve in hot and not pre cook.

At last, I am questioning about how the meat bun was made. You can saw that the bamboo steamer was dry compared to the Siumai one. The Siumai steamer was wet that mean at least the Siumai was steamed in it. Anyway, it was only my observation but mean nothing.', 'rating': '1'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I loved this place! In two weeks took the following: Chinese spring rolls (they were ok), Xiao Long Bao Shangai classic (the filling is very good and the dough is thick and fluffy), Char Siu Bao (basically the big dumplings, they are super tasty, I preferred these to the smaller ones), Aubergines Hong Shao (for sure the best thing we ate, they were delicious, I sincerely recommend these) and finally the Poulet Sweet & Sour (very good as well). We were very hungry and in the end we were quite full. Plus, the service was super kind and welcoming.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very very overrated, you can find better asian
restaurants in Paris. Never order the lemonade, it is just water. The mango sago is a mango lassi with very few tapioca perles and some small chunks of mango. Aubergines and noodles are ok.
Service was great. A shame that food wasn‚Äôt as good. Everything is deeply fried.', 'rating': '3'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Loved this great place. üòã
Great food, options even for vegans.
Big place so you can be spontaneous, friendly staff.
Enjoy', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This has to be one of THE HIDDEN GEMS of Paris. This isn‚Äôt on any tourist lists of places to eat and it‚Äôs not typical French food, but it is delicious and the vibe in this place is immaculate. We enjoyed it so much, we went back on our last night in Paris to have it again!  Beef Ho Fun is easily the best dish we had in Paris and the Sweet and Sour Chicken is unlike any version we‚Äôve had in the best way possible. Also, if you‚Äôre a dessert person, the lava French toast is a must try!  We would eat here again and again and will recommend this place to anyone traveling to Paris!', 'rating': '5'}]

name: JJAN
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'The food was very good, very close to authentic and the price for a Korean restaurant in Paris was quite ‚Äúaffordable‚Äù. The portions are big so it fills you well. It is a very popular restaurant so it gets crowded (even waiting lines outside) and there isn‚Äôt much space between tables. The staff is really nice and accommodating, if you need anything just ask and they will bring you.
Definitely recommend!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very good Korean dishes‚Äîtwo pages of choices. Love my spicy tofu soup. They need more vegetarian choices. The bibimbap bowl should be much hotter as the rice was room temperature so it made the dish less exciting.  Spartan furniture.', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Newly opened. Very tasty in a nicely designed restaurant.

Food wise : we got the dish to share. Cheese + chicken, some KFC as well.
It‚Äôs all good. Loved the fried chicken with their honey soy sauce.
Of course, they‚Äôll let you take everything in takeaway if you don‚Äôt finish.

Service wise : they just opened, when it‚Äôs full it gets a bit slow but I‚Äôm sure they‚Äôll improve very soon.

Price wise : I found it very affordable for that kind of Korean cuisine, especially considering it‚Äôs located in the very center of Paris.

I do recommend it.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great prices and great location. Small menu. We got the KFC and Budae Jigae- KFC was great and crispy and juicy. Budae came with two rice and we added spice so that was great. Nice sauce and was not too bad, 7/10. Service was quick.', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Food looks delicious but is somehow tasteless.
The kimchi pancake is extra oily.
The service was nice and friendly.
Overall atmosphere is loud and fun, good for an affordable dinner with friends if you are in the area and don‚Äôt care much for the food quality.', 'rating': '4'}]

name: Flam&go
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'It is a place where the food is delicious, the dishes are very good in size, the waiters are very friendly and serve you well, the craft beer is delicious, the decoration is spectacular.  It is a very nice and quiet place to dine.', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'When in Flam, you cannot really miss Aegir pub. A very cozy place (downstairs there is the ‚Äòpub‚Äô to enjoy a drink at the fireplace) whereas food is served upstairs. Recommended to reserve in advance (due to limited options in town, tends to get busy). We enjoyed the Viking plank - vegetarian and meat options. Both had 5 different dishes paired with 5 different beers. Overall very good flavors and enjoyed the experience. Food is plentiful.', 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': "The Hummus (Odin) was great, the fish the day before (cod) was rather okayish. The Service is sometimes just standing around and not checking if anyone wants something. The Beer tasting is nice, but the prices are quite high for rather standard quality in food and drinks. However, you will likely have no alternative since it is often the only open restaurant in Fl√•m. Better make a reservation, if not, you'll likely have to wait till you are seated upstairs in the restaurant. The ambiente is rustical Vikings Style, quite enjoyable.", 'rating': '4'}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very atmospheric place that you must visit when going to Fl√•m. My recommendation is the vega or regular plank with 5 courses and 5 beer tasting. Every beer combines with one of the flavours in the 5 courses. Really friendly staff as well!  The photos will tell your the rest!', 'rating': '5'}, {'author': '', 'text': "Food is generous, and the service is attentive. Portions are very generous and very well made. Love the decor and felt like I'm in a viking series set or even GoT. Highly recommended to make a trip here for a meal if you are in the area.", 'rating': '5'}]
